5. Longest Palindromic Substring
Java Solution
class Solution {
    int start = 0;
    int maxlen = 0;

    public String longestPalindrome(String s) {

        if (s == null || s.length() < 1) {
            return "";
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {

            // Odd length palindrome
            expand(s, i, i);

            // Even length palindrome
            expand(s, i, i + 1);
        }

        return s.substring(start, start + maxlen);
    }

    public void expand(String s, int left, int right) {

        while (left >= 0 &&
               right < s.length() &&
               s.charAt(left) == s.charAt(right)) {

            left--;
            right++;
        }

        int len = right - left - 1;

        if (len > maxlen) {
            maxlen = len;
            start = left + 1;
        }
    }
}
Problem Statement

Given a string s, return the longest palindromic substring present in the string.

A palindrome is a string that reads the same forward and backward.

Approach: Expand Around Center
Key Idea

Every palindrome has a center.

There are two possible palindrome types:

1. Odd Length Palindrome
aba
 ^

Center is a single character.

2. Even Length Palindrome
abba
 ^^

Center lies between two characters.

For every index:

Expand around (i, i) for odd-length palindromes.
Expand around (i, i + 1) for even-length palindromes.
Track the longest palindrome found.
Algorithm
Initialize:
start = 0
maxlen = 0
Iterate through each character of the string.
Expand around:
(i, i) → Odd palindrome.
(i, i + 1) → Even palindrome.
While characters match:
Move left pointer left.
Move right pointer right.
Calculate palindrome length.
Update longest palindrome if current length is larger.
Return substring from start to start + maxlen.
