Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
For every index, expansion can take up to O(n) time.
Total:
O(n²)
Space Complexity
O(1)

No extra data structures are used.

Key Learning
Every palindrome can be expanded from its center.
Check both odd and even length palindromes.
Use two pointers (left, right) to expand outward.
Keep track of the starting index and maximum length of the longest palindrome found.
GitHub Notes

Approach: Expand Around Center

Treat every character as the center of an odd-length palindrome.
Treat every pair of adjacent characters as the center of an even-length palindrome.
Expand outward while characters match.
Update the longest palindrome whenever a larger palindrome is found.
Return the substring using the stored starting index and maximum length.

Time Complexity: O(n²)
Space Complexity: O(1)
